<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>救生艇新闻：博客——保护人类</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Thu, 23 Apr 2026 12:59:09 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>帕金森病致病变异跨祖先分析和微阵列数据验证</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/parkinson-disease-pathogenic-variantscross-ancestry-analysis-and-microarray-data-validation</link><description>帕金森病致病变异：跨祖先分析和微阵列数据验证。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/parkinson-disease-pathogenic-variantscross-ancestry-analysis-and-microarray-data-validation2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 23 Apr 2026 12:59:06 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/parkinson-disease-pathogenic-variantscross-ancestry-analysis-and-microarray-data-validation</guid></item><item><title>长期与炎症相关的免疫分子可能有益于衰老的大脑</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/immune-molecule-long-tied-to-inflammation-may-benefit-the-aging-brain</link><description>大脑炎症通常被认为对衰老过程有害——它被认为会导致阿尔茨海默氏症和痴呆症。但一项针对小鼠的新研究表明，由一种名为 STING（干扰素基因刺激剂）的免疫分子引发的炎症可能在保护衰老的大脑方面发挥着作用。这些发现对于旨在阻断 STING 的新型实验性阿尔茨海默氏症药物也具有影响。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/immune-molecule-long-tied-to-inflammation-may-benefit-the-aging-brain2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 23 Apr 2026 12:44:06 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/immune-molecule-long-tied-to-inflammation-may-benefit-the-aging-brain</guid></item><item><title>HES1通过抑制NFATc2介导的炎症来调节骨髓间充质基质细胞功能</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/hes1-regulates-bone-marrow-mesenchymal-stromal-cell-function-by-suppressing-nfatc2-mediated-inflammation</link><description>骨髓微环境在造血和血液疾病中发挥着核心作用。一项新的研究调查了 HES1 如何调节间充质基质细胞功能和炎症信号传导，探索可能塑造造血稳态和疾病生物学的新途径。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/hes1-regulates-bone-marrow-mesenchymal-stromal-cell-function-by-suppressing-nfatc2-mediated-inflammation2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 23 Apr 2026 12:29:06 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/hes1-regulates-bone-marrow-mesenchymal-stromal-cell-function-by-suppressing-nfatc2-mediated-inflammation</guid></item><item><title>米氮平治疗甲基苯丙胺使用障碍：一项随机临床试验</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/mirtazapine-for-methamphetamine-use-disorder-a-randomized-clinical-trial</link><description>在患有甲基苯丙胺使用障碍的成年人中，与安慰剂相比，米氮平每月可将甲基苯丙胺的使用量减少大约两天，并且没有意外的安全问题。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/mirtazapine-for-methamphetamine-use-disorder-a-randomized-clinical-trial2.png" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 23 Apr 2026 12:14:06 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/mirtazapine-for-methamphetamine-use-disorder-a-randomized-clinical-trial</guid></item><item><title>你的大脑可能对现实视而不见，就像蚱蜢对微积分视而不见一样米歇尔·塞勒</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/your-brain-may-be-as-blind-to-reality-as-a-grasshopper-is-to-calculus-michelle-thaller</link><description>&lt;img src="https://politepol.com/fd/NjxHZtldG2if.xml" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 23 Apr 2026 11:59:06 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/your-brain-may-be-as-blind-to-reality-as-a-grasshopper-is-to-calculus-michelle-thaller</guid></item><item><title>人类不允许：科学人工智能代理拥有自己的社交网络</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/no-humans-allowed-scientific-ai-agents-get-their-own-social-network</link><description>自主代理不仅仅创建自己的研究——在 Reddit 风格的网站 Agent4Science 上，他们也在讨论它。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/no-humans-allowed-scientific-ai-agents-get-their-own-social-network.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 23 Apr 2026 11:44:06 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/no-humans-allowed-scientific-ai-agents-get-their-own-social-network</guid></item><item><title>初级手部运动皮层刺激对手指意志运动的频率依赖性影响</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/the-frequency-dependent-effects-of-primary-hand-motor-cortex-stimulation-on-volitional-finger-movement</link><description>[脑刺激] Taquet 等人：“运动皮层刺激对手指弯曲的影响与频率相关。” &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/the-frequency-dependent-effects-of-primary-hand-motor-cortex-stimulation-on-volitional-finger-movement.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 23 Apr 2026 11:29:06 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/the-frequency-dependent-effects-of-primary-hand-motor-cortex-stimulation-on-volitional-finger-movement</guid></item><item><title>程序性细胞死亡蛋白 1 (PD-1) 和程序性细胞死亡配体 1 (PD-L1) 免疫疗法：癌症治疗领域的重大突破</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/programmed-cell-death-protein-1-pd-1-and-programmed-cell-death-ligand-1-pd-l1-immunotherapy-a-promising-breakthrough-in-cancer-therapeutics</link><description>PD-1/PD-L1 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/programmed-cell-death-protein-1-pd-1-and-programmed-cell-death-ligand-1-pd-l1-immunotherapy-a-promising-breakthrough-in-cancer-therapeutics.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 23 Apr 2026 11:14:06 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/programmed-cell-death-protein-1-pd-1-and-programmed-cell-death-ligand-1-pd-l1-immunotherapy-a-promising-breakthrough-in-cancer-therapeutics</guid></item><item><title>氧-氧碰撞中夸克-胶子等离子体的最初迹象</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/first-signs-of-quark-gluon-plasma-in-oxygen-oxygen-collisions</link><description>当两个重原子核以相对论速度碰撞时，通常束缚在它们内部的夸克和胶子会短暂释放，形成一种称为夸克-胶子等离子体的奇异物质状态。当夸克和胶子穿过等离子体时，它们会通过散射损失能量，这限制了到达探测器的高动量粒子的数量。夸克-胶子等离子体的这种特征，称为喷射猝灭，只有在铅等重原子核的碰撞中才能被明确观察到，从而留下了一个悬而未决的问题：原子核必须有多大才能产生夸克-胶子等离子体。现在，CERN 大型强子对撞机 (LHC) 的 CMS 合作团队首次观察到氧-氧碰撞中射流猝灭的明确证据。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/first-signs-of-quark-gluon-plasma-in-oxygen-oxygen-collisions2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 23 Apr 2026 10:59:06 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/first-signs-of-quark-gluon-plasma-in-oxygen-oxygen-collisions</guid></item><item><title>74,000 年来，一位古代杀手悄悄决定了早期人类在非洲的生存地点</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/for-74000-years-one-ancient-killer-quietly-dictated-where-early-humans-could-survive-across-africa</link><description>越来越多的证据表明，我们的物种是通过生活在非洲不同地区的人群之间的相互作用而出现的，而不是来自一个单一的出生地。然而，到目前为止，大多数关于这些人口如何分布在非洲大陆的解释都只集中在气候上。新的研究表明，疾病——特别是疟疾——也发挥了至关重要的作用。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/for-74000-years-one-ancient-killer-quietly-dictated-where-early-humans-could-survive-across-africa.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 23 Apr 2026 10:44:06 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/for-74000-years-one-ancient-killer-quietly-dictated-where-early-humans-could-survive-across-africa</guid></item></channel></rss>